OL,3,CHeadteacher Neil Foden found guilty of
OL,4,Cchild sex abuse
OL,6,FHe was found not guilty of one charge
OL,7,Fof sexual activity with a child.After
OL,8,Fjust over a day of deliberation, the
OL,9,Fjury returned their verdict on
OL,10,FWednesday, 15 May, after an almost
OL,11,Ffour-week trial.Foden, who had denied
OL,12,Fall the charges, stared ahead as the
OL,13,Fverdicts were read out and showed no
OL,14,Femotion.
OL,16,FHe is due to be sentenced at Mold
OL,17,FCrown Court on Monday, 1 July.
OL,19,FJudge Rhys Rowlands warned he would go
OL,20,Fto jail and would receive a lengthy
OL,21,Fsentence.
