OL,3,CHeadteacher Neil Foden found guilty of
OL,4,Cchild sex abuse
OL,6,FThe judge told Foden "some of the
OL,7,Fexplanations for your behaviour
OL,8,Ftowards the victims proffered by you
OL,9,Fbeggared belief at times".
OL,11,FHe said he had shown himself to be
OL,12,F"arrogant" with a "controlling
OL,13,Fpersonality" and an "individual used
OL,14,Fto getting his own way".
OL,16,FHe added: "This defendant was arrogant
OL,17,Fand couldn't care less. He was Neil
OL,18,FFoden, a man in his view who could do
OL,19,Fno wrong."
